  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "description": {
        "text": "One of Sweden’s finest sport climbing crags, with high-quality routes for climbers of all abilities. The rock is solid, reddish granite. The climbing is varied, with vertical, slabby and overhanging terrain, and routes up to 25 m long. Mr. Big 6a+ and Solarplexus 7b+ are among the best of their kind in Sweden. In 1999, Anita Rostén made an impressive first on-sight ascent. There are also fantastic easier routes on Sjöväggen. The crag faces east and gets sun until 14:00 in summer. The best climbing season is from June to October. Many trees that shaded the walls have been felled, opening up the crag. It now dries more quickly. Six routes are particularly recommended; see the star rating *\n\nBolted routes graded 5–8",
        "method": "llm",
        "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
        "sourceIds": [
          "legacy:sjoanda"
        ]
      },
      "sections": {
        "allmant": {
          "title": {
            "text": "General information",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sjoanda"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "One of Sweden’s finest sport climbing crags, with high-quality routes for climbers of all abilities. The rock is solid, reddish granite. The climbing ranges from vertical and slabby to overhanging, with routes up to 25 m. Mr. Big 6a+ and Solarplexus 7b+ are among the best of their kind in Sweden. In 1999, Anita Rostén impressively made the first onsight ascent. There are also fantastic easier routes on the Lake Wall. The crag faces east and receives sun until 14:00 in summer. The best climbing season is June–October. Many trees that shaded the walls have been felled, opening up the crag. It now dries more quickly. Six routes are particularly recommended. See the star ratings *\n\nBolted routes graded 5–8",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sjoanda"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vagbeskrivning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Directions",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sjoanda"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The crag is approximately 44 km north-west of Västervik. From Västervik (44 km), take the E22 towards Gamleby. Take road 135 towards Kisa, turn right after 2 km onto road no. and continue for 5 km, then turn right at the sign for Sjöända 2. Turn right at the farm and park after 30 m by the parking sign. The path to the crag starts by the barn and is signposted to the right. The path is waymarked and the crag is on the left. Do not cross the meadows. The crag is 70 km from Linköping. Take road 35 and continue past Åtvidaberg. After 3 km, turn right onto road 134 towards Kisa. After approximately 1 km, turn left towards Dalhem. Follow the road for just over 26 km, pass Dalhem and turn left at the sign for Sjöända 2 km. Park on the right on the grassy area by the bend. Follow the 600 m path, which starts by the barn and enters the woods to the right of the parking area. The path is waymarked and the crag is on the left.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sjoanda"
            ]
          }
        },
        "overnattning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Accommodation",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sjoanda"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Cabins and a communal building are available from Risebo fritid, camping and cabins, tel. 0493-33046, http://www.risebofritid.se. Överums vandrarhem is approximately 10 km from the crag, tel. 0493-30302, http://www.overum.nu. KustCamp Gamleby, campsite, tel. 0493-10221, http://www.campa.se. Camping and cabins are available at Lysingsbadet in Västervik, tel. 0490-258000, http://www.lysingsbadet.se/. Cabins are also available from Tofvehults café och konferens, tel. 0490-26351, http://www.tofvehult.se, and Live in Nature at Kallersnäs gård, tel. 0768-513090, http://www.liveinnature.se",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sjoanda"
            ]
          }
        },
        "affarer": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Shops",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sjoanda"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The nearest supermarket, Coop, is in Överum, 13 km away. The nearest petrol stations, Preem and Bilia, are in Gamleby, 20 km away.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sjoanda"
            ]
          }
        },
        "klattercenter": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Climbing centre",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sjoanda"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The meeting place for climbers is the centre at Repslagargatan 5 in Västervik, by the old water tower. Free wireless internet is available, or you can borrow a computer. It is a place to meet, share experiences, read climbing magazines, watch climbing films and get up-to-date information about climbing and other activities in the municipality. You can also climb indoors and get to know other climbers. Call 0490-37466 for more information.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:sjoanda"
            ]
          }
        },
